					p
					strong Experiment
					|  :: Suppose I toss a fair die twice independently.
					br
					strong Random Variable
					|  :: X = Minimum of the two outcomes
					br
					strong Sample space S = {(i, j)|1 ≤ i, j ≤ 6}.
					br
					| Please note that the sample space has 36 elements and hence element has probability 1/36.
					br
					| The values X can take are {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}.
					br
					| X = i corresponds to the event {(i, i),(i, i + 1),(i + 1, i), . . . ,(i, 6),(6, i)}.
					br
					| Hence
					br
					| P(X = i) = (1 + (6 − i) ∗ 2)/36 =(13 − 2i)/36
					p
					br
					| Thus we can write the pmf as
					br
					| pX(x) = (13 − 2x)/36
					br
					| for x ∈ {1, 2, . . . , 6}

